<section id="fs-id2212351" class="free-response">
<title>Critical Thinking Questions</title>
<exercise id="fs-id2349123">
<problem id="fs-id2413241"><para id="fs-id2016531">Explain what happens to Na<sup>+</sup> concentration in the nephron when GFR increases.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id1482059"><label/>
<para id="fs-id2853934">Sodium concentration in the filtrate increases when GFR increases; it will decrease when GFR decreases.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1644341">
<problem id="fs-id2344681"><para id="fs-id1921296">If you want the kidney to excrete more Na<sup>+</sup> in the urine, what do you want the blood flow to do?</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id1587193"><label/>
<para id="fs-id2472434">To excrete more Na<sup>+</sup> in the urine, increase the flow rate.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
